@node features "Features"

                               Features

-Simple installation: just run the game and play!

-4 game board sizes to choose.

-Flecho is a "Workbench" game, so it is meant to be played on the
 Workbench screen. The game window can be resized up to a maximum of
 640 x 400 pixels, and the game is redisplayed according to the new
 window size. If the window is too small, it will automatically be
 resized to an adequate displayable size.

-As the game uses as little of the computer's ressources as possible,
 you can run other applications, games, etc. at the same time.

-Flecho works on all Amigas with Workbench 1.3 or higher.

@endnode

@node histo "History"

                               Versions History

  What follows are the various updates that were done since the first
version of this game.

1.0: -First public release.

1.01: -Bugfix: When the 'About' window was displayed and it overlapped
       the game board, the player could click on the tiles 'through'
       the About window.
      -Various changes were made to the program code.

1.02: Some changes have been made to the program code:
       -The routine that checks when the game window size is too small
        has been revised.
       -Now the player can quit the game by pressing 'q'.
       -Various other improvements have been made.

@endnode

@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Flecho" where you want on
your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or Libraries are
needed.

                             How to play?

  To play, just click on any arrow (the triangle-shaped icons), this will
rotate it by 45 degrees. If the right amount of arrows are pointing to a
number, that number will turn to white, otherwise it will remain black.
Obviously when there is a zero, no arrow should point to it. Continue the
game until all the numbers are in white, then the game will display how
many moves you made and a new game will start.

  An option allows you to choose the game board size from a 3 by 3 board
to a 6 by 6 board.

  You can restart the game anytime by clicking on the @{b}Restart@{ub} button.

  Have fun!

@endnode

